NPPES ZIP Code Analysis Plan
This plan outlines the steps to extract and analyze healthcare provider (HCP) density by ZIP code using the NPPES data.

Proposed Changes
[Data Processing]
[NEW] 
nppes_analyzer.py
A Python script to process the large NPPES CSV files efficiently.

Main File Processing:
Use pandas.read_csv with chunksize to handle the 11GB file.
Extract NPI and Provider Business Practice Location Address Postal Code.
Clean ZIP codes to 5 digits.
Practice Location File Processing:
Extract NPI and Provider Secondary Practice Location Address - Postal Code.
Clean ZIP codes to 5 digits.
Aggregation:
Combine (NPI, ZIP) pairs from both files.
Drop duplicates to ensure we count unique providers per ZIP.
Group by ZIP and count.
Output:
Save the resulting ZIP code counts to a JSON or CSV file for visualization.
Verification Plan
Automated Tests
Create a small subset of the NPPES data (e.g., first 1000 rows) to test the script.
Verify that the cleaning logic correctly handles 5-digit and 9-digit ZIP codes.
Verify that the aggregation correctly includes both primary and secondary practice locations.
Manual Verification
Check the top 10 ZIP codes by HCP count against known high-density areas (e.g., major medical centers).
Compare results with and without the Practice Location Reference File to quantify the "edge" mentioned by the user.
